Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "debeli" in different forms and positions:

1. *Debeli* čovek je sedeo na klupi u parku. (The *fat* man was sitting on a bench in the park.)
2. Oni su kupili *debelu* knjigu o istoriji srpske kulture. (They bought a *thick* book about the history of Serbian culture.)
3. Moja sestra ima jednu *debelu* mačku koja ne voli da se kreće. (My sister has a *fat* cat that doesn't like to move around much.)
4. Zimi, ljudi obično nose *debelu* odeću da bi se zaštitili od hladnoće. (In winter, people usually wear *thick* clothes to protect themselves from the cold.)
5. Njegov otac ima *debele* novčanice u novčaniku. (His father has *thick* banknotes in his wallet.)
6. Na pločniku su bili *debeli* slojevi snega koji su otežavali kretanje. (There were *thick* layers of snow on the pavement that made it difficult to walk.)
7. *Debeli* koren drveća virio je iz zemlje na ivici puta. (A *thick* tree root was sticking out of the ground at the edge of the road.)

I hope these examples help!